metadata.name: A Clock #168
metadata.description:
This generative token is based on a project I originally coded in late 2014, possibly my first creative project in JavaScript during graduate school at NYU ITP, which has run here since then: https://rossgoodwin.com/clock

The text in this case is not generated, but rather (legally) snipped from public domain e-books on Project Gutenberg (https://gutenberg.org/), and recontextualized as a real-time clock.

The editions vary in color palette and font choice, each with unique text for every minute determined by the clock's unique hash. For nearly all word/phrase blocks in the template system, there exist 512 possible excerpts you could receive, and countless possible combinations thereof. Additionally, 16 possible color palettes, 8 possible fonts, and many bezel types will determine your clock's visual appearance.

Unlike my original 2014 iteration, I wrote this clock in Vanilla JS with zero dependencies. (Largely, that's thanks to eight additional years of programming experience.) As a result, it's faster (once loaded) and more responsive as well.

metadata.name: Vertical World #68
metadata.description:
This artwork is a kind of my inquiry about ambiguous boundaries.
I was a child who liked to draw but always been dissatisfied with my work. Now through coding, I was able to create the "feelings" that I wanted to express. This work is not to imitate a certain landscape or painting style, but simply paint with different brushes, and cooperate with the randomness of the computer.
"I" creates horizontal order, and "computer" creates vertical disorder. My intention is to create
ambiguous visuals in a way that doesn't give specific images, but vague atmosphere.
The meaning is computer-generated and positioned through your eyes.
(It may take more time to render if you using Firefox browser.)

- Press [s] to save png image

Created by haxenfan using p5js.

metadata.name: Labyrinth #113
metadata.description:
The beginning of life is an incessant dream, a kaleidoscope of surprising discoveries, a colorful labyrinth in which you are enclosed by indefinitely high walls or a void, which you have to pass on your own. The person who may later become a guide through the labyrinth is still hiding behind some wall, past another turn. The main goal is to find him. If you succeed...


But you will succeed.

metadata.name: 10SCII #443
metadata.description:
10SCII is my take on the famous 10 PRINT program.

10 PRINT CHR$(205.5+RND(1)); : GOTO 10 is a single line program that produces a simple but visually appealing set of forward and backward slashes.

This project riffs on the original idea by removing the vertical space between lines and widening the horizontal gap. This changes the produced pieces from a maze of slashes into a series of towers. This is then rendered and animated as ASCII.

Visit https://10print.org/ to learn more about the original program that inspired this piece.

metadata.name: Kinetic Bug #228
metadata.description:
Best viewed on a decent GPU,  because physics simulations are performance intensive. Otherwise you might encounter a bug...

In a world of digital data, a new life is born. We are not alone...
Explore how kinetic bugs make their way through the world. What will their destiny be?
It's curious that we can sympathize to a predefined creature living it's predestined life in the digital world. Coding in the computer abyss reveals interesting worlds.

Keyboard
[ space ] - jump
[ click ] - increase velocity briefly
[ r ] - restart simulation
[ s ] - save image

metadata.name: Oil pastel #53
metadata.description:
A colorful oil pastel reminds me of my childhood, and the smooth feeling of oil pastel on paper. Therefore, this childhood experience motivated me to create this artwork in my generative art style.

-This artwork is a loop(animated). The height of oil pastels varied smoothly between two random heights.

-Left-clicking and dragging will rotate the camera position about the center of the sketch, right-clicking and dragging will pan the camera position without rotation.

-Various lighting color make the pastel colouration more diverse.

-Three different lightning methods were employed, as determined by characteristics.
The lighting color is chosen from nine colors coming from various types of sunlight.

metadata.name: FRAG || DEFRAG #107
metadata.description:
FRAG || DEFRAG is structured from the superposition of simple shapes, such as triangles, that alternate in different layers and blending modes. In this scenario, visual complexity is revealed at different times and intensities, offering countless possibilities of perception.

Along with this, the chromatic variation with unique gradations associated with the play of lights and shadows, gives the project different perspectives and depths, in continuous and complementary cycles of fragmentation and defragmentation.

Thus, as in everything that surrounds us, the resulting form does not end in itself, but presents itself as a result of the combination of several other distinct elements.

Nothing is just one thing.

#Main Features
- 13 color schemes âzonesâ:

* Shadow Sky and Bronze â 12,5% chance
* TIF, Soldier, Zreen and Ice â 10% chance each
* Vascai â 7,5% chance
* Burn Golden, Gray, Lemonade, REC and BR â 5% chance 
* 80âs â 2,5% chance

- 3 canvas formats;
- 3 frequency;
- 2 gradient type;
- 3 degrees of granulometry;

- 1 ultrarare feature | negative effect 

There is only a 1% chance of the negative effect appearing, if you are lucky you will see the following message. "YOU WIN A FREE EDITION OF MY NEXT PROJECT"

Obs.: 
- The first 5 iterations will entitle you to 1 free edition of my next project on FxHash.
- The rendering process should take a few seconds, so enjoy the look of the triangles in action.

July 30, 2022

Generative Token by Morbeck for fxhash.

metadata.name: Shattered Obelisks #51
metadata.description:
Shattered Obelisks began as a work that is dedicated to my habit of mindlessly drawing on paper when I am stressed, depressed or immersed in difficult thoughts.

Like a patient undergoing psychotherapy and piecing together the causes of unconscious fears and anxieties, I and my artwork have assembled ourselves into something shaped, found order in the chaos and separated it from the external noise.

It took 3 months of continuous, obsessive work. I have developed a huge library, designed for hand-like drawing. The functionality of this library is four times larger than what is shown in this drop.

I plan to put this library out into the public domain when I deem it complete, and hope that it will help someone express themselves through the creative process as much as it helped for me.

In case you've encountered a problem with inverted colours, try changing browser or disabling extensions. This problem only occurred once during testing on a massive amount of devices and was resolved by disabling extensions.

IMPORTANT NOTES BLOCK:

NOTE 1: This artwork should be viewed at a browser scale of 100%. Reducing the scale will increase the amount of detail, but may unpredictably affect the preservation of the location of secondary objects.

NOTE 2: This work can be printed on a plotter. Click S for saving it in .SVG.
Detailed instructions and answers to possible questions can be found in the console output of the code.

NOTE 3: This drop is the first one from the series of 3. It will be used as AL ticket in next drops of this series.

@abakshonokoleg
01.08.2022
